cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for automated tracking and quantification of myocardial motion and cardiac blood flow from echocardiograms. This involves image registration, which is a common problem in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The method also incorporates a neural network, which is a key component of deep learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper deals with medical imaging, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the method involves optimization of parameters, which is a common problem in neural networks and falls under the category of neural engineering (cs.NE).
